Great idea. Turning your template into an **agentic data science system** means the project will no longer be a fixed pipeline. Instead, **specialized AI agents collaborate to build, validate, train, and package the ML solution automatically**.

Think of the shift like this:

| Traditional DS Pipeline | Agentic DS Pipeline         |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------- |
| Static scripts          | Autonomous agents           |
| Sequential steps        | Decision-making workflow    |
| Manual debugging        | Self-diagnosing pipeline    |
| Fixed model training    | Model experimentation agent |

Let’s build a **practical architecture that fits your current template built with** Cookiecutter.

---

# 1. Core Idea of an Agentic Data Science Project

Instead of this:

```
data → features → train → predict
```

You create **intelligent agents** that decide what to do.

```
User Request
     ↓
Project Manager Agent
     ↓
Data Agent → Feature Agent → Training Agent → Evaluation Agent
     ↓
Packaging Agent
```

Each agent performs a **task + reasoning + validation**.

---

